Job Description:
* PURPOSE OF POSITION:
The F&B Business Development Manager is the Head of Department. S/he is the second in command after ED for the F&B Operations development management. 

* Major responsibilities include:
• Developing and implementing systems in place for monitoring compliance to established stores and service
standards;
• Ensuring that sales are conducted within the agreed financial parameters, performing feasibility studies on locations that seem suitable for the luxury market expansion;
• Setting measurable objectives for P&L, budgets, staff planning, etc; and –
• Setting and maintaining professional relationship with other departments, vendors and government entities.
* Key Responsibilities
* Business Strategies
• Illustrate and develop the annual plan, associated budgets and sales strategies;
• Optimize new and existing business opportunities to ensure business growth in line with the VF&B strategic plan;
• Develop and implement appropriate policies and procedures to cover key areas of operational activities;
• Devise yearly strategy and ensure that this is monitored, maintained and adjusted if needed;
• Monitor the Financial Costs, Expenses and ensure they are in adherence with the budget;
• Represent VF&B in front of business partners.
• Achieve Financial targets and business objectives as set by the Executive Director;
* Risk Assessment
• Ensure that business risks are identified, understood and monitored to mitigate the potential risks;
• Ensure the business complies with local laws and regulations;
* Marketing Campaign
• Develop and direct all chains' operation and promotional activities, and monitor the effectiveness of the marketing campaign;
* Team Leadership
• Provide regular coaching and mentoring to all team members;
• Hold performance review and feedback;
• Provide leadership, motivation and guidance to all staff in order to achieve growth and profitability targets;
• Develop team on hard and soft skills based on job requirement
• Perform other tasks assigned by direct supervisor.

